主帅无能，累死三军。LD她们分公司面临减员70%。总部也很难，安排不下几个人，下来的大部分面 ...<br />
<br />
Imperial Oil Ltd.’s surprise announcement Thursday that Bruce March is being replaced as company chairman, president and CEO by Rich Kruger (effective March 1, no less) had industry observers buzzing yesterday as to why the company’s majority shareholder – ExxonMobil – had decided to make a change at the top.<br />
<br />
The suspicion is that the change was made because March couldn’t control cost overruns at one of the Calgary-based company’s key growth projects – Kearl oil sands.<br />
<br />
The overruns have been substantial.<br />
<br />
Frankly, we had a lot of lessons learned!				<p class="author">
